item.description:
Compile Source code -&gt; object file: &ldquo;*.c -&gt; *.o&rdquo;
Link Object files -&gt; executable: &ldquo;*.o -&gt; a.out&rdquo;
makefile Rules target : prerequisites command1 command2 ... commandn   target is a target to be generated. It can be a object file, or a executable file or a label. prerequisites are dependecies of target. It is required to generate target. commandn are commands to generate target. Lines started with a &lsquo;\t&rsquo;  If any of prerequisites is newer than target, then make will call command1 to commandn.
